"Seize the moments of happiness, Love and be Loved!That is the only reality in the world, all else is folly!\n\n- Leo\n|\nThis is an Aston Martin, Gin.You don't run over dead bodies in an Aston Matin.''Tell that to James Bond\n\n- Jennifer Estep, Web of Lies\n|\nEducation is not a destination, but it is a curious journey to enjoy the beauty of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen you invest more time into something than others, you become the best among equals.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nAs soon as you trust yourself, you will know how to live.\n\n- Johann Wolfgang von Goethe, Faust: First Part\n|\nMom always said I was born to sit in the electric chair, but I'm proving her wrong. I'm going to die on my knees, begging for my life.\n\n- Bauvard, Some Inspiration for the Overenthusiastic\n|\nI've heard it said that God is in the details. It's the same with the truth. Leave out the details, the crucial heart, and you can damn someone with the bare bones of it.\n\n- Libba Bray, A Great and Terrible Beauty\n|\nYour vision is like a seed, which a sower sows in the ground\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThink of me as an impetuous Hegel, drunk with power, and also, regular drunk.\n\n- Eugene Mirman, The Will to Whatevs: A Guide to Modern Life\n|\nWhen love begs hatred & sorrow, show it your heart. For what you sow you reap, what you feel you seek.\n\n- Robert\n|\nwhen the need is in the mind, you cannot satisfy the need\n\n- Miguel Ruiz, The Mastery of Love: A Practical Guide to the Art of Relationship --Toltec Wisdom Book\n|\nOn occasions the war was like a Ping-Pong ball. You could put fancy spin on it, you could make it dance.\n\n- Tim\n|\nThere's nothing on Earth like really nailing the last line of a big book. You have 200 pages to tickle their fancy, and seven words to break their heart.\n\n- Alex\n|\nGod cannot and will not give us a sense of lasting pleasure apart from him, because it violates his purpose and our design. Psalm 34:8 reads, “Taste and see that the LORD is good.\n\n- Kyle Idleman, Gods at War: Defeating the Idols that Battle for Your Heart\n|\nHello, I'm Shellie's new boyfriend and I'm out of my mind. If you so much as talk to her or even think her name, I'll cut you in ways that'll make you useless to a woman.\n\n- Frank Miller, Sin City, Vol. 3: The Big Fat Kill\n|\nWe are all dying to give our lives away to something, maybe. God or Satan, politics or grammar, topology or philately (...) To games or needles, to some other person.\n\n- David Foster Wallace, Infinite Jest\n|\nTime is often wasted by those who don't understand that time is worth more than money because when lost, money can be regained but time cannot.\n\n- Gift\n|\nMaybe if I forgot things once in a while, we'd all be a little bit happier.\n\n- Jay Asher, Thirteen Reasons Why\n|\nSmartass Disciple: Master, why God let human did sins in the beginning?Master of Stupidity: If the saviour must come, why should He prevent that?\n\n- Toba\n|\nThe smile on his face said, pure and simple, those honey cakes came with a price. And his price was answers.\n\n- Melanie  Crowder, A Nearer Moon\n|\nHow often is happiness destroyed by preparation, foolish preparation!\n\n- Jane Austen, Emma\n|\nShe laughed, and he fell in love.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Slaying Dragons\n|\nWe often hear about stepping outside ourselves, but rarely about stepping outside our generation.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nIf we knew what it was we were doing, it would not be called research, would it?\n\n- Albert\n|\nIf you have no passion, you better do something different.\n\n- Alin\n|\nLife without books, chocolate & coffee is just useless.\n\n- Nadun\n|\nI write to make sense of my life.'-John Cheever, quoted in _Cheever - A Life_ (2009) by Blake Bailey\n\n- John\n|\nIf anyone understands, it's Jesus.\n\n- Kelli Rae Hurst, Man of Sorrows\n|\nI held the Host with two fingers and thought: How small Jesus made Himself, in order to show us that He doesn't expect great things of us, but rather little things with great love.\n\n- Mother\n|\nSome conjurers say that number three is the magic number, and some say number seven. It's neither my friend, neither. It's number one. (Fagin)\n\n- Charles Dickens, Oliver Twist\n|\nTo bring relevance to people, you have to be able to speak their language effectively\n\n- Sunday\n|\nFaith is always supposed to make it harder, not easier, to ignore the plight of our sisters and brothers. (p. 165)\n\n- Robin R. Meyers, Saving Jesus from the Church: How to Stop Worshiping Christ and Start Following Jesus\n|\nI simply regard romantic comedies as a subgenre of sci-fi, in which the world created therein has different rules than my regular human world.\n\n- Mindy Kaling, Is Everyone Hanging Out Without Me?\n|\nWith every part you act, there must be a little of yourself in it. If there isn't, it's not acting. It's lying.\n\n- Johnny\n|\nBooks gnaw at me from around the edges of my life, demanding more time and attention. I am always left hungry.\n\n- Pamela Paul, My Life with Bob: Flawed Heroine Keeps Book of Books, Plot Ensues\n|\nLike' and 'like' and 'like'--but what is the thing that lies beneath the semblance of the thing?\n\n- Virginia Woolf, The Waves\n|\nWords have the power to change us.' - Tessa Gray\n\n- Cassandra Clare, Clockwork Angel\n|\nSome people are like thorns. But you have to let them be thorns, because thorns can't turn into petals. The trick is not letting them prick you; never let a thorn prick you!\n\n- C.\n|\nFear and realisation of ignorance, strong medicines against stupid pride.\n\n- Garth Nix, Sabriel\n|\nLife never gives you what you want or need just because you have a burning desire for it. Life gives you what you seek, knock, and ask for.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nWhen the energy is directed outside, you create and manifest life outside, and when the same energy is directed inward, you reach to the ultimate truth of life.\