 The Awakening Wisdom of Life: Probably the best Quotation Book in the world\n|\nReceiving is good but giving is much better. Nevertheless, sharing is the best.\n\n- Shahrizad Shafian, Tunjuk Langit Cinta\n|\nBad things happen in life, but we must learn to deal with them and move on\n\n- Sid Mittra, To Bee or Not to Bee: Winning Against All Odds\n|\nJulia was as happy as Betsy was, almost. One nice thing about Julia was that she rejoiced in other people's luck.\n\n- Maud Hart Lovelace, Betsy and Tacy Go Downtown\n|\nState first, subject second, statesman last.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nWithout purpose, we're zombies aimlessly roaming the earth.\n\n- Ahmed\n|\nFeeling your way to knowledge rather than thinking your way, often results in better learning.\n\n- Sam Owen, 500 Relationships And Life Quotes: Bite-Sized Advice For Busy People\n|\nI need this wild life, this freedom.\n\n- Zane\n|\nThere is nothing that is going to make people hate you more, and love you more, than telling the truth.\n\n- Stefan\n|\nHaving defined your purpose and mission, you need to implement the program directly concerned with your goals every day\n\n- Sunday\n|\nOh Time, you arise with parting! [О Время, ты от разлуки!]- Vladislav Khalyavkin, The Operator\n\n- Vladislav\n|\nIf Nigeria will change for the better, then we must take responsibility for the changes in Nigeria.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nAll that two lovers want, is to be one with the other in a moment of ecstasy.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Art of Neuroscience in Everything\n|\nThe ramdomness of events in the world is so lacking in logic that we give it names like destiny, fate, karma and kismat to deal with the irrationality of its sequence\n\n- Anirban Bose, Bombay Rains, Bombay Girls\n|\nA soul that knows it is loved but does not itself love betrays its sediment: what is at bottom comes up.'―Epigrams and Interludes, Section 79\n\n- Friedrich Nietzsche, Beyond Good and Evil\n|\nAll resistance is a rupture with what is. And every rupture begins, for those engaged in it, through a rupture with oneself.\n\n- Alain Badiou, Metapolitics\n|\nI've never understood the desire for books with matched bindings. You don't go through life looking for sets of matched people, and books are just as individual.\n\n- Susan\n|\nSelf-discipline is a form of freedom. Freedom from laziness and lethargy, freedom from expectations and demands of others, freedom from weakness and fear -- and doubt.\n\n- H.A.\n|\nYou may receive a pie, eat it and forget. You may receive champagne, drink it and forget. But when you receive a book, you can open it again and again.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, 101 Keys To Everyday Passion\n|\nWe forget that the power of God isn’t in a weapon or a leader, but within us.\n\n- Toni Sorenson, Aligned By Christ\n|\nLawyers were notorious for finding cases in the most unlikely places, especially ones with huge potential damagers awards.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Handle with Care\n|\nWe all have a responsibility with the words we post on the internet. If you wouldn't want your mother, daughter, sister or friend to read it, don't post it.\n\n- Germany\n|\nIf you really want to buy greatness with time, you must invest the quality amount of time into your purpose and land of calling.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nI hope all you wish for comes to you,And you become who you're hoping to be.I know you will prosper in all you do,So promise you'll remember me.\n\n- Margo T. Rose, The Words\n|\nHappiness cannot be owned.It is in living in the spiritual experience of living every breath, that lets us taste a moment of it.\n\n- Mimi Novic, The Silence Between the Sighs\n|\nWe're all human, aren't we? Every human life is worth the same, and worth saving.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows\n|\nThere was the smell of old books, a smell that has a way of making all 