u may recall.\n\n- Lois McMaster Bujold, A Civil Campaign\n|\nThe perplexity, the potential— God’s own crucible was not for angels.\n\n- Johnny Worthen, Beatrysel\n|\nSchool has become the world religion of a modernized proletariat, and makes futile promises of salvation to the poor of the technological age.\n\n- Ivan Illich, Deschooling Society\n|\nI need someone who can be invisible, who can become a ghost. Do you think you can do that?'I'm already a ghost, she thought. I died in the hold of a slaver ship.'i think so.\n\n- Leigh Bardugo, Six of Crows\n|\nBecause even if the lie is beautiful, the truth is what you face in the end.\n\n- Lauren DeStefano, Fever\n|\nEvan always used to day that it wasn't that you couldn't see that you should be afraid of, but what was right in front of you, in plain sight.\n\n- Kathleen Glasgow, Girl in Pieces"